  "prompt": "What are the best free WordPress plugins in 2014?",
  "response": "In 2014, there were several popular and widely recommended free WordPress plugins that many users found valuable for enhancing their websites. Some of the best free WordPress plugins during that time included:\n\n1. **Yoast SEO**: One of the most widely used SEO plugins, offering a comprehensive solution for optimizing your website for search engines.\n\n2. **Wordfence Security**: A powerful security plugin that helped protect WordPress sites from malware, unauthorized login attempts, and other threats.\n\n3. **Jetpack by WordPress.com**: Offered a suite of features like enhanced security, site performance improvements, content tools, and visitor engagement options.\n\n4. **Contact Form 7**: A flexible and easy-to-use plugin for creating and managing contact forms on your website.\n\n5. **Akismet Anti-Spam**: Used to protect your comment section from spam, Akismet was often pre-installed with WordPress.\n\n6. **W3 Total Cache**: A performance optimization plugin that improved site speed by caching static files and enhancing server performance.\n\n7. **WooCommerce**: The most popular eCommerce plugin, allowing users to set up an online store with ease.\n\n8. **All in One SEO Pack**: Another strong SEO tool that provided similar functionalities to Yoast SEO, with easy configuration options to improve a site's SEO.\n\n9. **Google XML Sitemaps**: Automatically generated XML sitemaps to help search engines index your site more effectively.\n\n10. **NextGEN Gallery**: A popular plugin for managing image galleries with various display and management options.\n\nThese plugins were highly rated for their functionality, ease of use, and ability to address specific site needs, making them favorites among WordPress users in 2014.",
